<paragraph id="F45436C1FFEFFFB7FD89FB7EA999FA00" blockId="9.[136,1452,480,1582]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7FD89FB7EAC3DFAD2" bold="true" box="[189,348,1277,1303]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">Observations</emphasis>
: In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEFFFB7FF7EFB7DAF92FADC" author="Steudel, E. G." box="[586,755,1278,1305]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" refId="ref11485" refString="Steudel, E. G. (1855) Synopsis Plantarum Graminearum. J. B. Metzler, Stuttgart, 475 pp." type="book" year="1855">Steudel (1855)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the specimens used in the combination were collected by Lechler in Valdivia (
<collectingCountry id="8CFC7651FFEFFFB7FF36FAA3AF22FAFF" box="[514,579,1312,1338]" name="Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">Chile</collectingCountry>
; “Lechler legit Valdiviae”). 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEFFFB7FEB7FAA3A97EFAFE" author="Parodi, L. R." box="[899,1055,1312,1339]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" pagination="183 - 212" refId="ref10950" refString="Parodi, L. R. (1941) Revision de las gramineas sudamericanas del genero Hierochloe. Revista del Museo de La Plata (N. S.) 3 (14): 183 - 212." type="journal article" year="1941">Parodi (1941)</bibRefCitation>
proposed that the plant labelled as Lechler nº 246 from P (P- 
<date id="80551001FFEFFFB7FC87FAC0AF46FA98" box="[435,551,1347,1373]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" value="2772-02-30">02302772</date>
) should be considered the “typus”. Other plants collected by Lechler with the same number are stored in different herbaria, including B, W and S (B-100367031, W-18890070069, S-R-2927). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEFFFB7FC2BFA0BAF67FA66" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[287,518,1416,1443]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" refId="ref11638" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159] Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7FC48FA0AACCDFA67" box="[380,428,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, they must be considered 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFEFFFB7FE15FA0AAEE2FA66" box="[801,899,1417,1443]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">syntypes</typeStatus>
(Article 7.11, Ex. 13). We designate the specimen P- 
<date id="80551001FFEFFFB7FD94FA28AC70FA00" box="[160,273,1451,1477]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" value="2772-02-30">02302772</date>
as the 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFEFFFB7FC6BFA28ACA7FA00" box="[351,454,1451,1477]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">lectotype</typeStatus>
based on Article 9.17, Recommendation 9A (1&amp;2) (
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEFFFB7F924FA28A98CFA00" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1040,1261,1451,1478]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" refId="ref11638" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159] Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7F945FA2FA9C3FA00" box="[1137,1186,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F45436C1FFEFFFB7FD89FA4DA94EF9E8" blockId="9.[136,1452,480,1582]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEFFFB7FC1AFA4DAF55FA2D" author="Villalobos, N. &amp; Finot, V. &amp; Ruiz, E. &amp; Penailillo, P. &amp; Collado, G." box="[302,564,1486,1512]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" pagination="93 - 136" refId="ref11988" refString="Villalobos, N., Finot, V., Ruiz, E., Penailillo, P. &amp; Collado, G. (2019) Estudio morfometrico y taxonomico de las especies nativas chilenas del genero Anthoxanthum (Poaceae, Pooideae, Poeae, Anthoxanthinae). Darwiniana, Nueva Serie 7: 93 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.14522 / darwiniana. 2019.71.822" type="journal article" year="2019">
Villalobos 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7FC9DFA4CAC83FA2D" box="[425,482,1486,1512]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that morphological results do not justify the separation of this taxon from 
<taxonomicName id="33EB4D42FFEFFFB7FDF1FA72AC35F9CF" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1798" box="[197,340,1520,1546]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Torresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="utriculata">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7FDF1FA72AC35F9CF" box="[197,340,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">H. utriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7FC50FA73AFCEF9CF" box="[356,687,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">
sub 
<taxonomicName id="33EB4D42FFEFFFB7FCA5FA73AFCEF9CF" box="[401,687,1520,1546]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Antoxanthum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="utriculatum">Antoxanthum utriculatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
). However, molecular analyses (
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFEFFFB7F92FFA72A84EF9CE" author="Lema-Suarez, I. &amp; Sahuquillo, E. &amp; Estevez, G. &amp; Loureiro, J. &amp; Castro, S. &amp; Pimentel, M." box="[1051,1327,1520,1547]" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" pagination="389 - 413" refId="ref10670" refString="Lema-Suarez, I., Sahuquillo, E., Estevez, G., Loureiro, J., Castro, S. &amp; Pimentel, M. (2018) A taxonomic and evolutionary review of the South American Hierochloe sect. Monoecia Connor (Poaceae; Anthoxanthinae). Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 186: 389 - 413. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / botlinnean / box 102" type="journal article" year="2018">
Lema-Suarez 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7F98CFA72A989F9CF" box="[1208,1256,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
) recovered some variation for 
<taxonomicName id="33EB4D42FFEFFFB7FC68F997AC85F9E8" authorityName="Steudel" authorityYear="1855" box="[348,484,1555,1581]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Hierochloe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="altissima">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFEFFFB7FC68F997AC85F9E8" box="[348,484,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="101">H. altissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we consider that the varietal status is adequate.
</paragraph>
